    "Each model contained the following factors: Cosine Distance (measured by BERT), Sense Boundary (Same vs.",
    "Different Sense), Ambiguity",
    "Type (Homonymy vs. Polysemy), and an interaction between the latter two factors.",
    "The models differed in which measure of contextualized sensorimotor distance they used (i.e., relying on the human-generated vs. LLM-generated norms).",
    "First, both models achieved comparable fits (R 2 LLM = 0.718, R 2 human = 0.719)."
